nigeria chang auction rule to defend naira nigeria 's central bank ha chang the rule govern it foreign exchang auction in what analyst see as a mean of defend the naira currenc , which ha depreci steadili . the bank said in a statement that from april 2 , bank bid for foreign exchang would have to pay at the rate they offer and not , as present , at the rate of the lowest success bid made at the auction . thi should discourag bank from bid high to ensur that they were success while pay the lower `` margin `` rate , analyst said . the central bank also announc the auction would be fortnightli , not weekli , begin on april 2 .